1
00:00:54,791 --> 00:00:57,917
YUMI'S CELLS 3

2
00:01:00,458 --> 00:01:02,958
EPISODE 22
THE STICKLER

3
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:17,625
He's not here.

4
00:01:18,541 --> 00:01:20,042
Did he go out for lunch?

5
00:01:26,666 --> 00:01:27,666
Ms. Kim.

6
00:01:28,708 --> 00:01:30,416
Oh, Ms. Kim. You're here.

7
00:01:30,917 --> 00:01:32,625
- Hello.
- Gosh.

8
00:01:32,750 --> 00:01:34,083
You're early.

9
00:01:34,167 --> 00:01:35,375
Isn't the meeting at one?

10
00:01:35,750 --> 00:01:37,958
There was no traffic.

11
00:01:38,042 --> 00:01:39,791
Am I too early?

12
00:01:40,209 --> 00:01:41,375
Oh, not at all.

13
00:01:41,458 --> 00:01:43,334
The details aren't decided yet

14
00:01:43,416 --> 00:01:46,167
so feel free to tell us what you want.

15
00:01:46,250 --> 00:01:48,000
We'll incorporate everything you tell me.

16
00:01:48,708 --> 00:01:50,125
What do I know?

17
00:01:50,209 --> 00:01:52,083
You know best, Chief Editor Ahn.

18
00:01:52,167 --> 00:01:53,292
Ms. Kim.

19
00:01:53,375 --> 00:01:55,583
You need to review
these things carefully now.

20
00:01:55,666 --> 00:01:59,000
You're not the rookie writer
Kim Yu-mi anymore.

21
00:01:59,583 --> 00:02:02,167
I'm the same Kim Yu-mi as before.

22
00:02:02,250 --> 00:02:03,666
My, that's not true.

23
00:02:03,750 --> 00:02:05,416
Your aura is already different.

24
00:02:06,750 --> 00:02:09,000
LITERATURE RADIO

25
00:02:09,083 --> 00:02:10,083
By the way...

26
00:02:10,209 --> 00:02:12,250
But you're especially glowing today.

27
00:02:14,167 --> 00:02:15,334
Did something good happen?

28
00:02:16,666 --> 00:02:17,666
Sorry?

29
00:02:17,750 --> 00:02:20,625
Well, nothing that special happened...

30
00:02:21,209 --> 00:02:22,625
That's right, Ms. Kim.

31
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,250
Is Soon-rok...

32
00:02:25,625 --> 00:02:26,666
Soon-rok...

33
00:02:27,666 --> 00:02:28,666
Yes?

34
00:02:31,083 --> 00:02:32,083
Is he doing well?

35
00:02:32,167 --> 00:02:33,334
Is he not causing any trouble?

36
00:02:34,083 --> 00:02:35,334
Oh, not at all.

37
00:02:35,416 --> 00:02:36,416
He's doing well.

38
00:02:37,209 --> 00:02:38,541
Well, that's a relief.

39
00:02:38,625 --> 00:02:40,250
If there's even a tiny thing

40
00:02:40,334 --> 00:02:41,334
you don't like about him

41
00:02:41,708 --> 00:02:42,833
tell me right away.

42
00:02:42,958 --> 00:02:45,042
I've been keeping
a close eye on himlately.

43
00:02:46,541 --> 00:02:47,541
Why?

44
00:02:47,625 --> 00:02:50,500
I don't like his actions lately.

45
00:02:50,583 --> 00:02:53,125
He wasn't like this before,
but I guess he's gotten a big head.

46
00:02:53,209 --> 00:02:55,374
Well, he's doing well on our team

47
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:56,625
so don't worry.

48
00:02:56,750 --> 00:03:00,292
I tolerate him because he's a junior
I know and care for.

49
00:03:00,374 --> 00:03:01,374
But lately...

50
00:03:02,125 --> 00:03:03,750
Well, well. Look at that.

51
00:03:03,833 --> 00:03:05,750
Speak of the devil.

52
00:03:05,833 --> 00:03:07,083
It's Soon-rok!

53
00:03:07,250 --> 00:03:10,000
Soon-rok, did you have lunch?

54
00:03:13,625 --> 00:03:14,750
Ms. Kim came a while ago.

55
00:03:14,833 --> 00:03:16,083
Where have you been?

56
00:03:17,292 --> 00:03:18,416
Hello, Ms. Kim.

57
00:03:18,917 --> 00:03:20,083
Hello, Shin PD.

58
00:03:21,875 --> 00:03:25,333
JULLY LITERATURE RADIO

59
00:03:30,125 --> 00:03:32,000
Ms. Kim, would you like more coffee?

60
00:03:32,958 --> 00:03:34,083
No, I'm fine.

61
00:03:38,250 --> 00:03:39,958
The production team has arrived.

62
00:03:40,167 --> 00:03:41,167
They'll be up soon.

63
00:03:41,917 --> 00:03:42,917
Okay.

64
00:03:45,583 --> 00:03:46,666
By the way, Ms. Kim.

65
00:03:48,042 --> 00:03:49,042
Yes?

66
00:03:54,416 --> 00:03:55,625
You look pretty today.

67
00:04:00,750 --> 00:04:02,458
I always

68
00:04:03,167 --> 00:04:04,167
look this good.

69
00:04:04,541 --> 00:04:06,083
You have princess syndrome, don't you?

70
00:04:26,374 --> 00:04:27,416
But, Soon-rok.

71
00:04:28,541 --> 00:04:29,917
Don't you think

72
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:31,458
we should tell the Chief Editor?

73
00:04:34,167 --> 00:04:35,249
That we're dating?

74
00:04:35,541 --> 00:04:36,541
Yeah.

75
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,209
If he finds out later

76
00:04:38,291 --> 00:04:40,500
I think he'll feel really betrayed.

77
00:04:40,583 --> 00:04:42,374
I'll tell Ida,

78
00:04:42,458 --> 00:04:44,125
so you tell the Chief Editor.

79
00:04:44,416 --> 00:04:45,625
Absolutely not.

80
00:04:46,083 --> 00:04:47,083
If he finds out

81
00:04:47,708 --> 00:04:50,042
he might kick me out
of the Editorial Department.

82
00:04:50,125 --> 00:04:51,333
No way.

83
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:52,416
I'm serious.

84
00:04:52,541 --> 00:04:54,208
It's because of something I said before.

85
00:05:00,167 --> 00:05:01,500
You know

86
00:05:02,167 --> 00:05:03,625
producers who can't keep
work and life separate

87
00:05:03,708 --> 00:05:05,458
and date their writers?

88
00:05:05,917 --> 00:05:07,333
I think they're pathetic.

89
00:05:07,416 --> 00:05:10,666
How can they be objective about work?

90
00:05:11,666 --> 00:05:12,666
So?

91
00:05:13,167 --> 00:05:14,374
What did you say?

92
00:05:14,791 --> 00:05:15,791
They lack

93
00:05:16,583 --> 00:05:18,541
the basic sense of a producer.

94
00:05:18,750 --> 00:05:19,875
You think so too?

95
00:05:21,374 --> 00:05:22,374
People like that

96
00:05:22,625 --> 00:05:24,500
should be kicked out
of the Editorial Department.

97
00:05:25,625 --> 00:05:27,500
And last time in Busan...

98
00:05:28,167 --> 00:05:29,167
And?

99
00:05:31,708 --> 00:05:33,125
Toying with a writer's feelings

100
00:05:33,208 --> 00:05:35,374
for personal reasons is wrong.

101
00:05:35,458 --> 00:05:36,791
How is that toying with them?

102
00:05:36,875 --> 00:05:38,791
He was expressing his interest.

103
00:05:39,083 --> 00:05:40,083
I was rooting for him too.

104
00:05:40,166 --> 00:05:41,416
Was I toying with them too?

105
00:05:41,625 --> 00:05:43,333
Things like that can happen on a trip.

106
00:05:43,750 --> 00:05:45,083
I don't think that should happen.

107
00:05:46,291 --> 00:05:47,333
It's a workshop, after all.

108
00:05:49,042 --> 00:05:50,333
You should separate
your public and private life.

109
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:51,541
For goodness' sake.

110
00:05:51,625 --> 00:05:53,708
What a stick-in-the-mud.

111
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,750
You're so high and mighty, huh?

112
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:59,541
Acting like you've never had
an office romance in your life.

113
00:05:59,917 --> 00:06:01,125
I've never done that.

114
00:06:01,208 --> 00:06:03,042
Yeah, right. Not even a fling?

115
00:06:03,166 --> 00:06:04,708
I don't do that at work.

116
00:06:05,208 --> 00:06:06,208
Why not?

117
00:06:06,291 --> 00:06:07,833
- Sorry?
- Well, why not?

118
00:06:07,917 --> 00:06:09,125
It's not against rules.

119
00:06:09,750 --> 00:06:10,750
It's my principle.

120
00:06:10,833 --> 00:06:12,958
Principle, my foot.

121
00:06:13,042 --> 00:06:14,333
You just wait.

122
00:06:14,416 --> 00:06:17,124
If I ever catch you
having a fling, I'll just...

123
00:06:17,208 --> 00:06:18,666
That will never happen.

124
00:06:20,208 --> 00:06:21,875
Wait, you really said that?

125
00:06:23,208 --> 00:06:24,249
That's why we can't.

126
00:06:25,708 --> 00:06:27,708
Why did you say something
you couldn't keep?

127
00:06:28,333 --> 00:06:29,416
I was...

128
00:06:29,833 --> 00:06:31,124
- trying to.
- So...

129
00:06:31,416 --> 00:06:32,917
is that why you drew a line with me, too?

130
00:06:33,625 --> 00:06:34,625
But...

131
00:06:34,708 --> 00:06:37,583
you couldn't help it because of my charm.

132
00:06:38,958 --> 00:06:40,750
And you had no choice
but to break your principle.

133
00:06:41,249 --> 00:06:42,583
Because of a woman like me.

134
00:06:43,875 --> 00:06:44,875
That's what it was?

135
00:06:46,917 --> 00:06:49,708
You have a serious princess complex.

136
00:06:50,416 --> 00:06:51,583
You can't deny it, can you?

137
00:06:54,166 --> 00:06:55,166
Yu-mi.

138
00:06:55,249 --> 00:06:56,583
You said you wanted to go to Kyoto, right?

139
00:06:57,042 --> 00:06:58,082
Yeah, why?

140
00:06:58,374 --> 00:07:00,374
Want to go for two days
on Friday and Saturday?

141
00:07:01,082 --> 00:07:02,082
Because Saturday...

142
00:07:02,166 --> 00:07:03,166
is your birthday.

143
00:07:03,666 --> 00:07:04,666
Really?

144
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,291
I'd love to...

145
00:07:07,374 --> 00:07:08,374
Then I'll book the tickets.

146
00:07:08,458 --> 00:07:09,458
But I thought

147
00:07:09,708 --> 00:07:11,166
you had a trip to China today

148
00:07:11,249 --> 00:07:12,833
and were coming back on Friday?

149
00:07:13,291 --> 00:07:14,833
And you have another trip next week.

150
00:07:15,082 --> 00:07:16,958
I can just transfer flights
at the airport.

151
00:07:17,917 --> 00:07:19,416
That sounds like you're overdoing it.

152
00:07:19,875 --> 00:07:20,875
I'm fine.

153
00:07:20,958 --> 00:07:22,917
- We can go later.
- No.

154
00:07:23,124 --> 00:07:24,708
Going after your birthday

155
00:07:25,166 --> 00:07:26,541
doesn't count as a birthday present.

156
00:07:27,249 --> 00:07:28,249
Why?

157
00:07:28,333 --> 00:07:30,249
Because it goes against
one of Soon-rok's principles?

158
00:07:31,291 --> 00:07:32,291
I love it!

159
00:07:32,374 --> 00:07:34,042
If that's your principle, I love it.

160
00:07:35,500 --> 00:07:36,500
Let's go.

161
00:07:40,750 --> 00:07:42,000
You're here?

162
00:07:42,500 --> 00:07:43,583
- Come in.
- Hello.

163
00:07:44,041 --> 00:07:45,041
- Hello.
- Hello.

164
00:07:45,291 --> 00:07:46,291
- Hello.
- Hello.

165
00:07:46,374 --> 00:07:47,500
Hello.

166
00:07:48,208 --> 00:07:49,208
Indeed.

167
00:07:51,708 --> 00:07:54,000
If there's a castle for Writer Cell
in Yu-mi Village...

168
00:07:58,291 --> 00:08:01,333
there's an equally impressive tower
in Soon-rok Village.

169
00:08:05,500 --> 00:08:06,541
Its name?

170
00:08:08,625 --> 00:08:09,708
The Tower of Principles.

171
00:08:12,458 --> 00:08:14,249
It's the very symbol of Soon-rok Village.

172
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:18,875
This tower is built on the principles

173
00:08:18,958 --> 00:08:21,374
Soon-rok established over 29 years.

174
00:08:21,917 --> 00:08:23,791
And on each block, big and small

175
00:08:23,875 --> 00:08:26,666
important or trivial principles
are engraved.

176
00:08:26,750 --> 00:08:28,208
NO SINGLE USE PLASTIC FOR DELIVERIES
ONLY STRAWBERRY CUSTARD BUNGEOPPANG

177
00:08:28,291 --> 00:08:29,500
LAUNDRY ON WEDNESDAYS
PEACHES MUST BE FIRM

178
00:08:29,583 --> 00:08:30,625
Recently

179
00:08:30,708 --> 00:08:32,124
this tower has faced a crisis.

180
00:08:32,208 --> 00:08:33,958
Laundry on Wednesdays.

181
00:08:34,041 --> 00:08:35,041
What?

182
00:08:36,291 --> 00:08:37,291
Ms. Kim.

183
00:08:37,999 --> 00:08:39,041
Do you want to...

184
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:40,875
watch the movie together?

185
00:08:41,583 --> 00:08:43,416
Never see a movie alone with someone

186
00:08:43,791 --> 00:08:45,583
you have no romantic feelings for.

187
00:08:46,249 --> 00:08:48,291
A broken principle must be discarded.

188
00:08:51,166 --> 00:08:52,166
You're cool.

189
00:08:52,249 --> 00:08:53,500
Never make comments about a writer

190
00:08:53,583 --> 00:08:55,166
other than about their writing.

191
00:09:03,374 --> 00:09:04,666
Do not share an umbrella

192
00:09:04,750 --> 00:09:06,458
with a female colleague.

193
00:09:13,291 --> 00:09:14,291
Wait.

194
00:09:14,374 --> 00:09:16,583
Wait, hold on!

195
00:09:16,917 --> 00:09:18,708
You can't just pull them out like that.

196
00:09:18,875 --> 00:09:20,708
What if the tower shakes?

197
00:09:20,791 --> 00:09:22,750
NO MATTER HOW CUTE,
DON'T CARELESSLY PET ANOTHER'S DOG

198
00:09:27,708 --> 00:09:30,082
See? It's shaking.

199
00:09:30,166 --> 00:09:31,166
I know.

200
00:09:32,416 --> 00:09:34,458
But a broken principle...

201
00:09:37,666 --> 00:09:39,666
must be discarded as that's the principle.

202
00:09:40,625 --> 00:09:42,791
Hold on, this is a crisis.

203
00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:45,916
Soon-rok's principles
should never be broken.

204
00:09:45,999 --> 00:09:47,666
How many is that already?

205
00:09:48,500 --> 00:09:50,082
All because of Writer Kim Yu-mi?

206
00:09:51,583 --> 00:09:53,999
This is why you need to draw the line.

207
00:09:58,166 --> 00:10:00,708
The crisis didn't end there.

208
00:10:06,374 --> 00:10:08,916
Don't cancel plans at the last minute.

209
00:10:09,124 --> 00:10:11,374
Hey, let go.

210
00:10:11,458 --> 00:10:13,333
Do not argue during work.

211
00:10:14,249 --> 00:10:15,500
I think I...

212
00:10:16,416 --> 00:10:17,750
I think

213
00:10:17,833 --> 00:10:19,291
I like you, Writer.

214
00:10:20,166 --> 00:10:21,625
Don't confess romantic feelings to a woman

215
00:10:21,708 --> 00:10:23,082
you have professional ties with.

216
00:10:32,124 --> 00:10:34,374
- He's crazy.
- He's gone nuts.

217
00:10:34,541 --> 00:10:36,541
He actually confessed to a writer.

218
00:10:36,625 --> 00:10:37,708
What do we do?

219
00:10:37,791 --> 00:10:39,208
- It'll collapse if he pulls that out.
- Is it gonna collapse?

220
00:10:39,291 --> 00:10:40,625
Be careful!

221
00:11:10,416 --> 00:11:12,082
This is too dangerous.

222
00:11:12,374 --> 00:11:13,791
If even one more comes out,

223
00:11:13,874 --> 00:11:15,291
it could collapse at any moment.

224
00:11:15,374 --> 00:11:17,124
Do something about Writer Yu-mi.

225
00:11:17,541 --> 00:11:18,791
I drew the line.

226
00:11:18,999 --> 00:11:21,333
I even put up an absolute defense.
What more can I do?

227
00:11:21,458 --> 00:11:22,625
Rational!

228
00:11:22,957 --> 00:11:24,333
Look at Soon-rok.

229
00:11:25,916 --> 00:11:27,208
No matter how much I think about it, I...

230
00:11:30,750 --> 00:11:31,957
I like you, Writer.

231
00:11:33,583 --> 00:11:35,500
It's pathetic
I've only just realized, but...

232
00:11:36,999 --> 00:11:38,166
Perhaps from the very beginning...

233
00:11:40,957 --> 00:11:42,708
I think I've liked you.

234
00:11:43,458 --> 00:11:46,041
THE TOWER OF PRINCIPLES

235
00:11:46,791 --> 00:11:48,291
Don't make a move on a woman

236
00:11:48,541 --> 00:11:50,374
who has rejected you.

237
00:11:53,500 --> 00:11:56,208
He went to see Writer Yu-mi again.

238
00:11:56,291 --> 00:11:57,957
DON'T MAKE A MOVE ON A WOMAN
WHO HAS REJECTED YOU

239
00:12:06,249 --> 00:12:08,416
- It's collapsing! It's collapsing!
- Oh, no.

240
00:12:14,708 --> 00:12:16,999
DON'T MAKE A MOVE ON A WOMAN
WHO HAS REJECTED YOU

241
00:12:27,374 --> 00:12:28,790
LAUNDRY ON WEDNESDAYS

242
00:12:30,957 --> 00:12:31,957
Oh, no!

243
00:12:47,874 --> 00:12:49,583
Just look at that disgraceful sight!

244
00:12:49,790 --> 00:12:52,625
This is the first time it's happened
in Soon-rok's 29 years of life.

245
00:12:52,916 --> 00:12:54,832
To think the tower
is in danger of collapsing.

246
00:12:54,916 --> 00:12:56,458
I'm sorry.

247
00:12:56,749 --> 00:12:59,208
I tried drawing lines

248
00:12:59,291 --> 00:13:02,999
and going on dates to keep my distance...

249
00:13:03,790 --> 00:13:06,999
but Writer Yu-mi's influence
is too strong...

250
00:13:07,082 --> 00:13:08,625
What's so special about Kim Yu-mi?

251
00:13:08,999 --> 00:13:10,374
Is Kim Yu-mi the priority?

252
00:13:10,458 --> 00:13:11,874
Or are the principles the priority?

253
00:13:12,708 --> 00:13:13,874
Soon-rok's principles

254
00:13:13,957 --> 00:13:15,583
are his identity.

255
00:13:19,291 --> 00:13:21,999
He's painstakingly built them up
for 29 years.

256
00:13:23,458 --> 00:13:25,082
If they collapse...

257
00:13:26,749 --> 00:13:29,583
then Soon-rok is no longer Soon-rok.

258
00:13:32,458 --> 00:13:33,500
That's right.

259
00:13:36,374 --> 00:13:38,208
FRIDAY

260
00:13:44,416 --> 00:13:45,625
I wonder if he's arrived.

261
00:13:53,416 --> 00:13:54,749
I guess he's not here yet.

262
00:13:55,249 --> 00:13:56,249
Yu-mi.

263
00:13:58,041 --> 00:13:59,041
Soon-rok.

264
00:13:59,291 --> 00:14:00,291
Have you arrived?

265
00:14:00,374 --> 00:14:01,874
I just landed.

266
00:14:02,208 --> 00:14:03,790
I just arrived at the airport too.

267
00:14:03,957 --> 00:14:06,333
It'll be crowded,
so let's meet inside after security.

268
00:14:06,625 --> 00:14:08,583
I'll get my bags and head right over.

269
00:14:09,249 --> 00:14:10,291
Okay.

270
00:14:10,374 --> 00:14:11,458
I can't wait to see you.

271
00:14:14,707 --> 00:14:16,416
- See you soon.
- Okay.

272
00:14:16,999 --> 00:14:17,999
Bye.

273
00:14:21,249 --> 00:14:22,832
Gosh, how many days has it been?

274
00:14:22,916 --> 00:14:24,790
It's almost been a whole week.

275
00:14:25,082 --> 00:14:26,082
Hurry up.

276
00:14:26,166 --> 00:14:27,500
Let's go see Soon-rok.

277
00:14:27,999 --> 00:14:29,082
I'm going.

278
00:14:43,166 --> 00:14:44,291
- This way.
- Thank

279
00:14:53,041 --> 00:14:54,082
you. Where are you?

280
00:14:55,166 --> 00:14:56,208
I've boarded.

281
00:15:03,333 --> 00:15:04,374
I'm at the gate.

282
00:15:04,707 --> 00:15:05,874
I'll head in soon.

283
00:15:20,541 --> 00:15:22,500
It's really been a while
since I've played golf.

284
00:15:22,582 --> 00:15:23,665
I know, right? It's been so long.

285
00:15:23,749 --> 00:15:25,124
By the way, will you go to duty-free?

286
00:15:25,208 --> 00:15:26,582
Which gate is ours?

287
00:15:26,665 --> 00:15:27,874
Are you going to duty-free?

288
00:15:32,166 --> 00:15:33,166
Did you see

289
00:15:33,249 --> 00:15:34,624
who just walked by?

290
00:15:35,832 --> 00:15:37,291
No, I didn't see.

291
00:15:37,374 --> 00:15:39,208
Why? Did a celebrity walk by?

292
00:15:39,291 --> 00:15:40,291
Who?

293
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:44,582
Emergency, emergency!

294
00:15:54,999 --> 00:15:56,166
Soon-rok.

295
00:15:56,458 --> 00:15:57,458
What do we do?

296
00:16:00,333 --> 00:16:01,333
Hey.

297
00:16:03,124 --> 00:16:04,166
Soon-rok.

298
00:16:11,208 --> 00:16:13,082
Hey, what are you doing here?

299
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:14,500
Hello.

300
00:16:14,832 --> 00:16:16,582
Hold on. Ju-ho!

301
00:16:17,249 --> 00:16:18,249
Ju-ho!

302
00:16:24,624 --> 00:16:25,665
What's this?

303
00:16:28,291 --> 00:16:29,582
- Whoa, whoa.
- Hello.

304
00:16:29,665 --> 00:16:31,208
Wait, wait. What are you doing here?

305
00:16:31,540 --> 00:16:32,957
Where are you going now?

306
00:16:33,291 --> 00:16:35,832
Didn't you just tell me
you got back from Shanghai?

307
00:16:36,458 --> 00:16:38,624
Yes... yes, I did.

308
00:16:38,916 --> 00:16:40,500
So where are you off to again?

309
00:16:41,208 --> 00:16:42,291
- Well, it's just...
- Yeah?

310
00:16:43,082 --> 00:16:44,082
Well...

311
00:16:44,249 --> 00:16:46,707
I already had a trip scheduled.

312
00:16:46,916 --> 00:16:48,208
So you're going on another trip

313
00:16:48,291 --> 00:16:49,333
without even stopping by home?

314
00:16:49,582 --> 00:16:51,665
I booked it a long time ago.

315
00:16:53,707 --> 00:16:54,707
What?

316
00:16:54,790 --> 00:16:56,582
Do you get it? Because I don't.

317
00:16:57,749 --> 00:16:59,874
He's young, so I guess it's possible.

318
00:16:59,957 --> 00:17:01,291
Where are you two headed?

319
00:17:01,374 --> 00:17:03,374
- Our golf club's regular tour.
- I see.

320
00:17:03,458 --> 00:17:05,499
Sir, I'll check your seat for you.

321
00:17:05,624 --> 00:17:06,707
- Oh, yes.
- Yes.

322
00:17:07,999 --> 00:17:09,790
- Anyway, see you later.
- Okay.

323
00:17:13,416 --> 00:17:15,041
- It's a window seat.
- Yes.

324
00:17:15,832 --> 00:17:17,957
Hey, it's fine. Just come on, get in.

325
00:17:28,041 --> 00:17:29,416
Is he traveling alone?

326
00:17:29,499 --> 00:17:30,499
You think he's alone?

327
00:17:30,582 --> 00:17:31,582
He is.

328
00:17:31,665 --> 00:17:33,749
That empty seat is taken.

329
00:17:33,832 --> 00:17:35,208
- Who?
- Who do you think?

330
00:17:35,291 --> 00:17:39,249
Who else would be this passionate
even after a business trip?

331
00:17:40,665 --> 00:17:42,624
Is that it?

332
00:17:43,124 --> 00:17:44,333
So he has a girlfriend?

333
00:17:45,166 --> 00:17:46,208
Since when?

334
00:17:46,540 --> 00:17:48,166
He travels with his woman

335
00:17:48,249 --> 00:17:49,749
but won't let others have a fling?

336
00:17:50,540 --> 00:17:51,624
Selfish jerk.

337
00:17:54,124 --> 00:17:56,874
Soon-rok, Kim Ju-ho, and Chief Editor Ahn

338
00:17:56,957 --> 00:17:58,582
are on our plane.

339
00:17:58,665 --> 00:17:59,707
What do we do?

340
00:18:06,499 --> 00:18:09,333
THE TOWER OF PRINCIPLES

341
00:18:13,082 --> 00:18:15,499
BARLEY TEA OVER BOTTLED WATER

342
00:18:17,374 --> 00:18:20,874
Don't date coworkers,
and don't get caught.

343
00:18:21,166 --> 00:18:24,041
This is Soon-rok's Grand Principle
of Grand Principles.

344
00:18:24,499 --> 00:18:25,499
If this one gets broken...

345
00:18:28,124 --> 00:18:29,166
It's all over.

346
00:18:30,082 --> 00:18:31,999
The tower collapses.

347
00:18:42,082 --> 00:18:43,082
Hello?

348
00:18:43,166 --> 00:18:44,832
Yu-mi, why aren't you getting on?

349
00:18:45,457 --> 00:18:46,499
Those two got on, right?

350
00:18:48,082 --> 00:18:49,082
They did.

351
00:18:49,624 --> 00:18:51,665
Of all the flights,
how could we be on the same one?

352
00:18:51,749 --> 00:18:53,540
- I shouldn't get on.
- What?

353
00:18:54,291 --> 00:18:56,041
What am I supposed to do
with Ju-ho there too?

354
00:18:56,124 --> 00:18:57,415
I think you'll get in trouble.

355
00:18:57,499 --> 00:18:59,874
- I won't get on.
- What will you do if you don't?

356
00:18:59,957 --> 00:19:02,208
I'll just take the next flight.
There are plenty of flights to Osaka.

357
00:19:02,291 --> 00:19:03,499
No, no. Yu-mi, wait.

358
00:19:03,916 --> 00:19:05,457
Then I'll get off right now.

359
00:19:05,540 --> 00:19:07,415
Soon-rok. Meet me at the airport.

360
00:19:07,499 --> 00:19:08,540
I'll be right behind you.

361
00:19:10,749 --> 00:19:11,749
Hello? Yu-mi.

362
00:19:16,582 --> 00:19:19,749
Arah Air Flight 701 to Osaka.

363
00:19:19,832 --> 00:19:22,499
- We'll be closing the cabin doors.
- Sir, please be seated.

364
00:19:23,208 --> 00:19:25,624
- I'm sorry but...
- Ju-ho! Look at him.

365
00:19:25,707 --> 00:19:26,707
What's with him?

366
00:19:26,957 --> 00:19:28,957
We will close the door shortly.

367
00:19:29,999 --> 00:19:31,291
I guess he's really going alone.

368
00:19:32,041 --> 00:19:33,373
You really think that?

369
00:19:33,457 --> 00:19:36,373
- He is.
- No, his girlfriend's waiting in Osaka.

370
00:19:37,291 --> 00:19:39,499
Oh, is that it?

371
00:19:40,624 --> 00:19:41,874
Ladies and gentlemen

372
00:19:41,957 --> 00:19:44,665
our plane will now be taking off.

373
00:19:45,082 --> 00:19:48,790
Please check that
your seatbelts are fastened.

374
00:19:49,957 --> 00:19:53,499
Yu-mi prevented Soon-rok's
principle from collapsing.

375
00:19:56,291 --> 00:19:57,291
However...

376
00:20:01,874 --> 00:20:04,291
Dear passengers, welcome to Osaka

377
00:20:04,373 --> 00:20:06,665
a city for all seasons.

378
00:20:07,041 --> 00:20:08,582
The current local time is...

379
00:20:08,790 --> 00:20:09,790
Yu-mi, where are you?

380
00:20:10,957 --> 00:20:11,999
I just arrived.

381
00:20:16,999 --> 00:20:18,332
WRITER KIM YU-MI

382
00:20:18,874 --> 00:20:20,249
- Yu-mi.
- Soon-rok.

383
00:20:20,582 --> 00:20:22,457
- I can't make it.
- What?

384
00:20:22,916 --> 00:20:24,373
There are no tickets.

385
00:20:24,749 --> 00:20:26,499
I mean, there are so many flights

386
00:20:26,582 --> 00:20:28,166
but not a single ticket is available.

387
00:20:28,290 --> 00:20:30,249
They're all sold out
until tomorrow morning.

388
00:20:30,749 --> 00:20:31,749
So...

389
00:20:32,082 --> 00:20:34,208
I'm on my way home now.

390
00:20:34,624 --> 00:20:36,290
Well, it's the weekend.

391
00:20:36,624 --> 00:20:39,249
That's why you should've taken the flight.

392
00:20:40,249 --> 00:20:41,249
For a two-day trip

393
00:20:41,332 --> 00:20:44,790
there's no point
in flying tomorrow afternoon, right?

394
00:20:45,790 --> 00:20:46,957
What should I do?

395
00:20:47,166 --> 00:20:49,373
You're there, so just have fun.

396
00:20:49,457 --> 00:20:50,707
- Okay?
- No, that's...

397
00:20:50,832 --> 00:20:51,832
Shin PD.

398
00:20:57,166 --> 00:20:58,332
Don't tell me you got stood up.

399
00:20:59,874 --> 00:21:00,874
Right?

400
00:21:03,041 --> 00:21:05,124
Your girlfriend is waiting for you
at the airport, isn't she?

401
00:21:05,582 --> 00:21:07,707
You didn't really come on this trip
alone, did you?

402
00:21:08,124 --> 00:21:10,124
Hey, I said that's not it.

403
00:21:10,208 --> 00:21:12,373
Shin PD is different from us.

404
00:21:13,041 --> 00:21:14,332
Jeez.

405
00:21:16,499 --> 00:21:17,499
Take care.

406
00:21:17,832 --> 00:21:19,248
- Call me.
- Let's go.

407
00:21:20,373 --> 00:21:21,373
Gosh, I'm so stiff.

408
00:21:21,457 --> 00:21:23,957
My body isn't what it used to be.

409
00:22:02,290 --> 00:22:03,916
When using the hot spring

410
00:22:03,999 --> 00:22:06,457
we recommend that you stay hydrated.

411
00:23:18,123 --> 00:23:21,290
To all our passengers,
thank you for flying with us.

412
00:23:21,373 --> 00:23:24,457
Our plane has arrived at its destination.

413
00:23:24,749 --> 00:23:26,957
Please remain seated until the plane
comes to a complete stop

414
00:23:27,041 --> 00:23:31,332
and the seatbelt sign has been turned off.

415
00:23:31,874 --> 00:23:34,041
Soon-rok, call me when you arrive.

416
00:23:34,332 --> 00:23:35,582
I'm here to pick you up.

417
00:23:43,665 --> 00:23:44,707
Soon-rok!

418
00:23:56,999 --> 00:23:58,081
I could've just taken the bus.

419
00:23:58,165 --> 00:23:59,832
I still came because I wanted to see you.

420
00:24:01,749 --> 00:24:02,749
I'll drive.

421
00:24:03,081 --> 00:24:04,081
Will you?

422
00:24:04,457 --> 00:24:05,457
A present.

423
00:24:05,832 --> 00:24:07,874
What's this? Oh, snacks.

424
00:24:08,415 --> 00:24:09,749
Let's have them with some beer.

425
00:24:13,665 --> 00:24:15,582
How could they have been

426
00:24:15,665 --> 00:24:17,999
on that specific flight out of so many?

427
00:24:18,999 --> 00:24:20,373
We're so unlucky, really.

428
00:24:21,123 --> 00:24:22,790
I wanted to visit Kyoto.

429
00:24:29,582 --> 00:24:30,749
What did you do there?

430
00:24:31,332 --> 00:24:33,165
I took a bath, ate, and slept.

431
00:24:33,624 --> 00:24:35,123
Then I woke up, ate

432
00:24:35,332 --> 00:24:36,957
took a bath, and came back.

433
00:24:39,123 --> 00:24:40,290
You got some good rest.

434
00:24:40,373 --> 00:24:41,832
Yes, I did.

435
00:24:46,290 --> 00:24:47,290
Are you mad?

436
00:24:48,874 --> 00:24:50,999
- No.
- Why do you seem mad?

437
00:24:51,415 --> 00:24:53,582
It's not something
I should be mad at you for.

438
00:24:56,707 --> 00:24:59,207
I was so upset too.

439
00:24:59,332 --> 00:25:00,790
Can you imagine how I felt?

440
00:25:00,957 --> 00:25:02,916
I had to turn back right at the gate.

441
00:25:04,207 --> 00:25:07,081
But I did it because I was worried
you'd be in a difficult position.

442
00:25:07,665 --> 00:25:10,707
You insisted on separating work
and private life so many times.

443
00:25:10,957 --> 00:25:12,582
If we couldn't get caught like that

444
00:25:13,499 --> 00:25:14,998
you have your image to keep, too.

445
00:25:17,499 --> 00:25:18,540
That stupid principle.

446
00:25:26,499 --> 00:25:27,540
Where are you going?

447
00:25:53,665 --> 00:25:55,290
Who are you calling?

448
00:25:55,373 --> 00:25:57,123
SHIN SOON-ROK PD

449
00:25:57,540 --> 00:25:59,040
- Hello?
- Hello?

450
00:25:59,624 --> 00:26:01,373
Dae-yong, it's Soon-rok.

451
00:26:02,415 --> 00:26:03,790
I have something to tell you.

452
00:26:03,874 --> 00:26:04,956
Sure, what is it?

453
00:26:06,040 --> 00:26:07,040
I'm...

454
00:26:07,749 --> 00:26:09,290
dating Writer Kim Yu-mi.

455
00:26:14,123 --> 00:26:15,332
Wait, what?

456
00:26:15,749 --> 00:26:17,290
I'm dating Writer Kim Yu-mi.

457
00:26:18,040 --> 00:26:19,081
It's been a while.

458
00:26:22,248 --> 00:26:24,457
What... what did you just say?

459
00:26:24,540 --> 00:26:25,956
So just know that.

460
00:26:26,624 --> 00:26:28,665
I'll tell you the details later.

461
00:26:29,665 --> 00:26:30,665
Have a nice trip!

462
00:26:31,832 --> 00:26:32,915
Hello... hello?

463
00:26:41,415 --> 00:26:45,123
GRAND PRINCIPLE
DON'T DATE COWORKERS AND DON'T GET CAUGHT

464
00:26:47,373 --> 00:26:49,707
TOWER OF PRINCIPLES

465
00:27:22,665 --> 00:27:23,873
Yu-mi.

466
00:27:23,956 --> 00:27:25,582
We can go on trips whenever we want now.

467
00:27:25,665 --> 00:27:27,457
Hey, what are you doing? Your principle...

468
00:27:27,540 --> 00:27:30,373
I'm throwing away that stupid
principle and everything.

469
00:27:31,040 --> 00:27:32,540
What's the point of having principles?

470
00:27:32,832 --> 00:27:34,040
They're going to be broken anyway.

471
00:27:36,832 --> 00:27:37,873
Because of me?

472
00:27:38,749 --> 00:27:40,749
Are all of your principles being broken

473
00:27:40,832 --> 00:27:41,956
because of me?

474
00:27:43,290 --> 00:27:44,915
Because you like me that much?

475
00:27:47,457 --> 00:27:49,248
Can you stop being so full of yourself?

476
00:27:51,749 --> 00:27:52,790
What are you going to do?

477
00:27:53,956 --> 00:27:56,415
All your precious principles
are broken because of me...

478
00:27:58,373 --> 00:28:00,998
I didn't mean for that to happen.

479
00:28:01,373 --> 00:28:03,540
I wanted to protect
your precious principles...

480
00:28:13,749 --> 00:28:14,749
But, Soon-rok

481
00:28:15,165 --> 00:28:16,873
I feel really great right now.

482
00:28:17,373 --> 00:28:19,415
Better than a birthday gift
or a trip to Kyoto

483
00:28:19,499 --> 00:28:21,248
I feel amazing right now.

484
00:28:22,123 --> 00:28:23,165
I feel great too.

485
00:28:48,582 --> 00:28:50,040
And so, the Tower of Principles

486
00:28:50,123 --> 00:28:51,582
in Soon-rok Village collapsed.

487
00:28:52,789 --> 00:28:54,415
Conquered by Yu-mi

488
00:28:55,998 --> 00:28:58,540
now only its ruins remain.

489
00:28:59,499 --> 00:29:01,081
Conquered by Yu-mi

490
00:29:01,290 --> 00:29:03,457
on her birthday.

491
00:29:05,624 --> 00:29:08,998
EPISODE 23
A ONE-WAY LIFE

492
00:29:11,081 --> 00:29:12,123
Hello.

493
00:29:14,373 --> 00:29:15,415
Hello.

494
00:29:17,956 --> 00:29:18,998
Hello.

495
00:29:24,081 --> 00:29:25,540
Shin PD, you're here.

496
00:29:26,081 --> 00:29:27,123
Yes.

497
00:29:27,207 --> 00:29:29,248
The Chief Editor has been looking for you.

498
00:29:29,707 --> 00:29:31,248
He told me to let him know
the moment you got in.

499
00:29:31,831 --> 00:29:33,499
Just a moment. I need to send an email.

500
00:29:33,956 --> 00:29:36,165
Shin Soon-rok, you're being summoned.

501
00:29:39,956 --> 00:29:41,123
Did you do something wrong?

502
00:29:43,248 --> 00:29:44,248
I'm not sure.

503
00:30:01,373 --> 00:30:02,624
Did you have a good golf trip?

504
00:30:02,706 --> 00:30:05,873
Whether I had a good trip or not
is none of your business.

505
00:30:06,332 --> 00:30:07,373
Hey, you punk.

506
00:30:08,499 --> 00:30:10,831
PDs who can't separate work and life

507
00:30:10,915 --> 00:30:12,915
PDs who date their writers...

508
00:30:13,123 --> 00:30:14,582
Didn't you say they should all be fired?

509
00:30:14,998 --> 00:30:16,706
That they have no basic principles?

510
00:30:16,789 --> 00:30:18,457
Didn't you say that?

511
00:30:20,373 --> 00:30:22,081
Huh? I remember all of it.

512
00:30:22,373 --> 00:30:24,873
You said you wouldn't have a fling.
That that was your principle, right?

513
00:30:26,081 --> 00:30:27,624
- I did.
- And?

514
00:30:27,706 --> 00:30:28,873
Well...

515
00:30:29,831 --> 00:30:31,373
A person's principles

516
00:30:32,373 --> 00:30:33,706
can change, can't they?

517
00:30:35,040 --> 00:30:36,081
What? What did you say?

518
00:30:36,165 --> 00:30:38,956
People's minds change.

519
00:30:43,040 --> 00:30:44,664
How can this punk be so shameless?

520
00:30:44,748 --> 00:30:46,207
We're human because we change.

521
00:30:46,332 --> 00:30:47,332
Otherwise, we'd be robots.

522
00:30:47,415 --> 00:30:48,624
Hey, look at this punk.

523
00:30:50,956 --> 00:30:52,040
Are you laughing?

524
00:30:52,332 --> 00:30:53,706
What's so funny?

525
00:30:54,415 --> 00:30:55,873
Sorry, but I have an urgent email.

526
00:30:55,956 --> 00:30:57,582
Can we talk after I send it?

527
00:30:57,664 --> 00:30:59,664
- Are you trying to get away?
- I need to reschedule

528
00:30:59,748 --> 00:31:01,457
tomorrow's meeting from Shanghai.

529
00:31:01,540 --> 00:31:03,123
Shanghai? Right, you take care of that.

530
00:31:03,248 --> 00:31:05,165
All right. Then let's talk over lunch.

531
00:31:05,248 --> 00:31:06,664
I can't have lunch with you.

532
00:31:06,789 --> 00:31:07,873
Why not?

533
00:31:07,956 --> 00:31:10,081
Who do you think you are,
turning down lunch?

534
00:31:10,248 --> 00:31:11,956
-I have something to take care of.
-Why?

535
00:31:12,040 --> 00:31:13,040
Are you going on a date?

536
00:31:14,040 --> 00:31:15,081
Not exactly.

537
00:31:15,915 --> 00:31:17,706
I haven't gotten her
a birthday present yet.

538
00:31:18,873 --> 00:31:20,956
If I go on my business trip today

539
00:31:21,040 --> 00:31:22,373
I won't see her for another week.

540
00:31:23,748 --> 00:31:27,040
Wow, just... So openly like this?

541
00:31:27,540 --> 00:31:28,956
You weren't this kind of guy before.

542
00:31:31,207 --> 00:31:32,664
I've always been this kind of guy.

543
00:31:33,457 --> 00:31:34,457
It's just that

544
00:31:34,540 --> 00:31:36,165
my direction has changed.

545
00:31:39,873 --> 00:31:41,332
The Tower of Principles

546
00:31:41,415 --> 00:31:42,748
the symbol of Soon-rok Village.

547
00:31:44,540 --> 00:31:48,582
This tower was guarded by a warrior
named the One-Way General.

548
00:31:52,248 --> 00:31:53,290
Watch out!

549
00:31:55,165 --> 00:31:57,831
When the Tower of Principles,
which he had long guarded, collapsed

550
00:31:59,581 --> 00:32:01,207
the One-Way General, now purposeless

551
00:32:01,623 --> 00:32:02,623
was flustered.

552
00:32:04,123 --> 00:32:05,123
What should I...

553
00:32:05,207 --> 00:32:06,664
protect now?

554
00:32:07,664 --> 00:32:10,706
If he wasn't protecting
something worth devoting his life to

555
00:32:11,040 --> 00:32:13,457
he was a cell with no reason to exist.

556
00:32:19,207 --> 00:32:21,499
He finally made a decision.

557
00:32:28,789 --> 00:32:30,873
The conqueror of love
who destroyed the tower.

558
00:32:35,581 --> 00:32:38,207
He vows to protect Yu-mi.

559
00:32:47,415 --> 00:32:48,457
Welcome.

560
00:32:50,539 --> 00:32:51,831
Can I help you find something?

561
00:32:53,165 --> 00:32:54,789
I'm looking for women's earrings.

562
00:32:54,873 --> 00:32:56,207
Sure, this way.

563
00:32:58,998 --> 00:33:00,998
Do you have a particular style in mind?

564
00:33:01,706 --> 00:33:02,706
Well...

565
00:33:03,040 --> 00:33:04,165
It's a birthday present.

566
00:33:04,248 --> 00:33:05,332
For your girlfriend?

567
00:33:06,040 --> 00:33:08,581
- Yes.
- What's your girlfriend's taste?

568
00:33:10,415 --> 00:33:12,415
I'm not sure about her taste

569
00:33:13,956 --> 00:33:15,831
but I'm sure she won't like anything big.

570
00:33:15,956 --> 00:33:17,207
So she doesn't like big pieces.

571
00:33:17,290 --> 00:33:18,748
Because her face is tiny.

572
00:33:19,373 --> 00:33:21,581
So big ones wouldn't suit her.

573
00:33:21,664 --> 00:33:22,998
Oh, I see.

574
00:33:23,081 --> 00:33:24,498
So she has a small face.

575
00:33:25,998 --> 00:33:28,123
It's as small as a fist.

576
00:33:29,290 --> 00:33:30,581
And she has fair skin.

577
00:33:32,332 --> 00:33:33,332
Right.

578
00:33:33,623 --> 00:33:35,332
Her face is very small and fair.

579
00:33:35,664 --> 00:33:36,915
Oh, right.

580
00:33:38,457 --> 00:33:40,123
Do you need more information?

581
00:33:40,207 --> 00:33:41,290
Oh, yes.

582
00:33:41,623 --> 00:33:43,831
Then it's easier for me
to make a recommendation.

583
00:33:46,623 --> 00:33:47,915
She's the intellectual type.

584
00:33:48,664 --> 00:33:49,789
And elegant...

585
00:33:50,748 --> 00:33:51,748
Also...

586
00:33:53,789 --> 00:33:55,040
she's pretty when she smiles.

587
00:33:55,457 --> 00:33:56,457
She's slim.

588
00:33:56,748 --> 00:33:58,664
No, more like slender.

589
00:34:00,248 --> 00:34:01,748
The kind that makes you

590
00:34:02,623 --> 00:34:03,831
want to protect her.

591
00:34:05,748 --> 00:34:06,748
I see.

592
00:34:10,332 --> 00:34:11,332
Do you have any earrings

593
00:34:11,415 --> 00:34:12,873
that would suit that style?

594
00:34:13,332 --> 00:34:16,123
These designs are very popular these days.

595
00:34:16,373 --> 00:34:19,498
Since she's intellectual, elegant,
and has a small face

596
00:34:19,873 --> 00:34:21,248
I think a simple design is better

597
00:34:21,332 --> 00:34:23,539
- than something too flashy.
- Yes.

598
00:34:41,165 --> 00:34:42,539
One-Way General!

599
00:34:42,623 --> 00:34:44,081
Come back!

600
00:34:44,207 --> 00:34:45,748
- The One-Way General Cell
- That's not the way!

601
00:34:45,831 --> 00:34:48,165
- started walking down a new path.
- That's not the way!

602
00:34:50,414 --> 00:34:52,123
One-Way General!

603
00:34:52,539 --> 00:34:53,873
I'm not going back.

604
00:34:54,207 --> 00:34:55,207
I've already

605
00:34:55,290 --> 00:34:57,248
chosen this path.

606
00:35:09,373 --> 00:35:11,123
Would you like to see something else?

607
00:35:13,789 --> 00:35:14,789
Can you

608
00:35:14,998 --> 00:35:16,539
show me this one?

609
00:35:30,998 --> 00:35:31,998
Yu-mi.

610
00:35:37,414 --> 00:35:39,040
You should've waited inside. It's hot.

611
00:35:39,414 --> 00:35:40,664
The weather was so nice

612
00:35:40,748 --> 00:35:42,414
I waited outside on purpose.

613
00:35:42,831 --> 00:35:44,165
But why were you coming from over there?

614
00:35:46,123 --> 00:35:47,123
I was just looking at something.

615
00:35:48,664 --> 00:35:50,664
The Chief Editor is at work, right?

616
00:35:50,748 --> 00:35:51,789
Was everything okay?

617
00:35:52,789 --> 00:35:54,539
I was questioned for over an hour.

618
00:35:54,623 --> 00:35:55,915
A whole hour?

619
00:35:56,081 --> 00:35:57,748
What kind of interrogation
takes a whole hour?

620
00:35:58,831 --> 00:36:00,623
Let's talk on the way.

621
00:36:01,248 --> 00:36:02,998
I have to be at the airport by 9 o'clock.

622
00:36:03,789 --> 00:36:05,332
Then we don't have much time.

623
00:36:05,539 --> 00:36:07,414
We should eat first. Let's hurry.

624
00:36:07,498 --> 00:36:08,873
There are many good places here.

625
00:36:08,956 --> 00:36:10,581
Wait, not here.

626
00:36:11,081 --> 00:36:13,331
Let's go to a famous spot nearby.

627
00:36:13,539 --> 00:36:15,915
- A famous spot?
- It's close to here. Let's go.

628
00:36:19,123 --> 00:36:20,539
But there are other places here.

629
00:36:20,623 --> 00:36:21,748
That place is good too.

630
00:36:28,623 --> 00:36:29,706
It's a must-visit spot

631
00:36:29,789 --> 00:36:31,456
whenever I'm in this neighborhood.

632
00:36:32,331 --> 00:36:33,456
You'll like it too.

633
00:36:34,498 --> 00:36:35,706
What kind of place is it?

634
00:36:35,915 --> 00:36:36,915
It's a bunsik restaurant.

635
00:36:37,331 --> 00:36:38,789
It's 30 years old

636
00:36:39,498 --> 00:36:40,831
and the tteokbokki is amazing.

637
00:36:41,248 --> 00:36:43,040
I love tteokbokki.

638
00:36:44,998 --> 00:36:46,040
Wait a minute.

639
00:36:46,706 --> 00:36:48,123
Something feels...

640
00:36:48,207 --> 00:36:49,207
That's right.

641
00:36:49,956 --> 00:36:51,123
It's definitely

642
00:36:51,498 --> 00:36:52,789
this alley.

643
00:36:56,207 --> 00:36:58,248
What's the name of that place?

644
00:36:59,414 --> 00:37:00,414
The name?

645
00:37:01,040 --> 00:37:02,165
It's...

646
00:37:04,165 --> 00:37:05,623
I can't remember it all of a sudden.

647
00:37:06,498 --> 00:37:07,581
It was an English name.

648
00:37:08,207 --> 00:37:09,414
An English name?

649
00:37:09,748 --> 00:37:10,789
Hold on.

650
00:37:10,998 --> 00:37:12,956
We aren't going there, right?

651
00:37:13,207 --> 00:37:14,207
It's this way.

652
00:37:18,831 --> 00:37:19,873
We're here.

653
00:37:22,831 --> 00:37:23,956
I knew it!

654
00:37:24,331 --> 00:37:25,539
Oh, right.

655
00:37:25,623 --> 00:37:26,956
Yes, it's Ba-bi's Snack Bar.

656
00:37:27,748 --> 00:37:29,581
It's my regular spot.
Why couldn't I remember it?

657
00:37:30,248 --> 00:37:32,331
This is your regular spot?

658
00:37:32,873 --> 00:37:33,873
Yes.

659
00:37:33,998 --> 00:37:36,247
You'll be so surprised when you try it.

660
00:37:36,623 --> 00:37:37,623
Let's go.

661
00:37:42,289 --> 00:37:44,247
- Let's go somewhere else.
- Why?

662
00:37:44,748 --> 00:37:45,748
But you said you love tteokbokki.

663
00:37:46,207 --> 00:37:47,207
I do.

664
00:37:47,956 --> 00:37:48,956
But...

665
00:37:49,040 --> 00:37:50,664
I'm full.

666
00:37:50,998 --> 00:37:52,581
Or do you want to go eat by yourself?

667
00:37:52,664 --> 00:37:54,915
I'll wait for you at that coffee shop.

668
00:37:55,165 --> 00:37:56,247
What are you talking about?

669
00:37:56,789 --> 00:37:57,915
You have to try this

670
00:37:57,998 --> 00:37:59,331
even if you're full.

671
00:37:59,998 --> 00:38:02,539
- Come on, let's go.
- No, wait. I really...

672
00:38:02,664 --> 00:38:03,664
Wait a second.

673
00:38:15,414 --> 00:38:18,748
BA-BI'S SNACK BAR

674
00:38:18,831 --> 00:38:20,956
CLOSED FOR VACATION FOR A WEEK
07/24 - 07/31

675
00:38:24,539 --> 00:38:26,206
They're on vacation.

676
00:38:28,539 --> 00:38:31,498
Let's go somewhere else.
I know another good tteokbokki place.

677
00:38:41,289 --> 00:38:43,247
Thank goodness it's closed.

678
00:38:43,331 --> 00:38:46,165
It would've been so awkward
if I ran into Ba-bi's dad.

679
00:38:52,831 --> 00:38:54,498
Hunger Cell. Isn't this your appetite?

680
00:38:55,456 --> 00:38:56,956
I was so surprised earlier

681
00:38:57,040 --> 00:38:58,456
that I dropped it.

682
00:38:58,831 --> 00:39:00,498
Then what's that on your head now?

683
00:39:02,748 --> 00:39:05,539
My appetite grows back once I calm down.

684
00:39:06,372 --> 00:39:08,539
CELL SNACK

685
00:39:14,831 --> 00:39:16,372
- This place is delicious too.
- Right?

686
00:39:16,581 --> 00:39:17,831
This place is pretty famous too.

687
00:39:18,040 --> 00:39:19,372
I should get some to go on my way out.

688
00:39:19,456 --> 00:39:21,873
But they don't do takeout here.

689
00:39:25,539 --> 00:39:26,956
Ba-bi's Snack Bar does takeout.

690
00:39:32,414 --> 00:39:33,831
This place is good

691
00:39:34,040 --> 00:39:35,331
but it can't beat Ba-bi's Snack Bar.

692
00:39:35,789 --> 00:39:37,956
The combination of green onions
and broth there

693
00:39:38,414 --> 00:39:39,414
is amazing.

694
00:39:43,414 --> 00:39:45,498
I didn't know

695
00:39:45,915 --> 00:39:47,873
you were so serious about tteokbokki.

696
00:39:51,706 --> 00:39:52,748
By the way...

697
00:39:53,998 --> 00:39:55,206
why were you acting like that earlier?

698
00:39:58,040 --> 00:39:59,206
Why were you so against

699
00:39:59,915 --> 00:40:01,915
going into Ba-bi's Snack Bar?

700
00:40:08,414 --> 00:40:09,414
It's...

701
00:40:09,498 --> 00:40:10,498
complicated.

702
00:40:10,664 --> 00:40:11,664
What is it?

703
00:40:15,122 --> 00:40:16,623
What should I do?

704
00:40:16,956 --> 00:40:18,789
Soon-rok noticed.

705
00:40:18,873 --> 00:40:20,080
Tell him.

706
00:40:20,206 --> 00:40:22,206
Soon-rok is Yu-mi's boyfriend now.

707
00:40:22,706 --> 00:40:24,331
There should be no lies between them.

708
00:40:26,956 --> 00:40:27,998
The truth is...

709
00:40:29,206 --> 00:40:30,206
That place...

710
00:40:32,040 --> 00:40:34,539
It's run by my ex-boyfriend's father.

711
00:40:34,915 --> 00:40:36,456
I've been there before.

712
00:40:36,956 --> 00:40:38,247
So it's a bit awkward

713
00:40:39,040 --> 00:40:40,164
for me to go there.

714
00:40:45,080 --> 00:40:46,080
Wait a minute.

715
00:40:52,664 --> 00:40:54,164
Then your ex-boyfriend...

716
00:40:55,789 --> 00:40:56,831
His name is Ba-bi?

717
00:40:58,247 --> 00:40:59,247
Is that right?

718
00:40:59,956 --> 00:41:00,956
Yeah, it is.

719
00:41:02,581 --> 00:41:04,998
That's right. So it is.

720
00:41:05,498 --> 00:41:06,581
The owner said

721
00:41:06,664 --> 00:41:10,039
he named the shop after his son.

722
00:41:11,706 --> 00:41:13,915
Oh, I see. I guessed Ba-bi right.

723
00:41:17,331 --> 00:41:18,581
I see.

724
00:41:19,873 --> 00:41:20,873
But...

725
00:41:21,164 --> 00:41:22,748
I know his son.

726
00:41:23,080 --> 00:41:24,831
- You know him?
- Yes.

727
00:41:25,331 --> 00:41:27,080
I saw him at the counter a few times.

728
00:41:28,372 --> 00:41:29,372
But...

729
00:41:29,831 --> 00:41:30,998
that guy...

730
00:41:32,748 --> 00:41:34,706
He was really handsome.

731
00:41:36,039 --> 00:41:37,539
- No, he wasn't.
- No.

732
00:41:37,623 --> 00:41:39,247
He was very handsome.

733
00:41:39,623 --> 00:41:40,998
That's why I remember him.

734
00:41:44,289 --> 00:41:45,372
What's going on?

735
00:41:45,456 --> 00:41:47,414
Soon-rok looks upset.

736
00:41:49,498 --> 00:41:51,206
He seems to care too much.

737
00:41:53,539 --> 00:41:54,581
He was just...

738
00:41:55,372 --> 00:41:56,706
average.

739
00:41:57,664 --> 00:41:58,706
Just a very average...

740
00:41:58,789 --> 00:41:59,789
You really...

741
00:42:06,247 --> 00:42:07,289
do care about looks.

742
00:42:18,456 --> 00:42:19,748
Yeah, that's right.

743
00:42:20,331 --> 00:42:21,331
I do care about looks.

744
00:42:22,247 --> 00:42:24,122
Soon-rok, thanks for your looks.

745
00:42:25,289 --> 00:42:26,539
It's all thanks to my parents.

746
00:42:29,498 --> 00:42:32,498
I'm glad my Soon-rok
is so understanding about it.

747
00:42:32,873 --> 00:42:34,955
I can't tell if he's being
innocent or cool, though.

748
00:42:37,331 --> 00:42:40,289
What a relief. My appetite is back.

749
00:42:45,748 --> 00:42:47,372
One-Way General.

750
00:42:47,623 --> 00:42:49,456
Don't just keep going forward.

751
00:42:50,289 --> 00:42:52,456
It's about her ex-boyfriend.

752
00:42:54,414 --> 00:42:56,748
Could it be that guy we heard about?

753
00:42:56,831 --> 00:42:58,831
The one who fell for a young intern

754
00:42:58,915 --> 00:43:00,206
so they broke up.

755
00:43:00,372 --> 00:43:01,664
What does it matter?

756
00:43:01,748 --> 00:43:04,289
I've already chosen this path.

757
00:43:04,664 --> 00:43:05,914
But still...

758
00:43:06,456 --> 00:43:08,039
aren't you curious?

759
00:43:09,247 --> 00:43:10,247
Out of my way.

760
00:43:13,623 --> 00:43:15,414
Only the one-way life.

761
00:43:21,164 --> 00:43:22,206
What was that?

762
00:43:24,289 --> 00:43:26,456
The One-Way General kept to his path

763
00:43:27,164 --> 00:43:29,164
and finally reached his destination.

764
00:43:30,122 --> 00:43:32,289
Who is that?
Is it one of Soon-rok's cells?

765
00:43:32,539 --> 00:43:34,080
It's not the Love Cell.

766
00:43:34,873 --> 00:43:35,873
- Who are you?
- Who are you?

767
00:43:43,414 --> 00:43:45,080
- What?
- What? I asked who you are.

768
00:43:50,247 --> 00:43:51,872
A fist-sized face!

769
00:43:54,206 --> 00:43:56,581
Skin as fair as snow!

770
00:43:59,122 --> 00:44:00,206
What was that?

771
00:44:00,289 --> 00:44:02,164
A fist-sized face

772
00:44:02,247 --> 00:44:05,206
with snow-white skin.

773
00:44:05,414 --> 00:44:08,539
Born with intelligence and grace.

774
00:44:09,872 --> 00:44:12,955
The one with a million-dollar smile

775
00:44:13,039 --> 00:44:16,498
and so delicate that she makes you
want to protect her!

776
00:44:21,623 --> 00:44:22,914
The conqueror

777
00:44:23,623 --> 00:44:25,080
Kim Yu-mi!

778
00:44:28,623 --> 00:44:29,623
What's going on?

779
00:44:30,247 --> 00:44:32,456
I am One-Way General

780
00:44:32,539 --> 00:44:35,581
guardian of Soon-rok Village.

781
00:44:35,914 --> 00:44:38,830
Please open these castle
gates wide and clear a path

782
00:44:38,914 --> 00:44:41,914
so that I may walk a one-way road
for you my entire life

783
00:44:41,997 --> 00:44:44,997
and protect you.

784
00:44:46,955 --> 00:44:48,331
One-Way General Cell?

785
00:44:48,414 --> 00:44:50,206
That cell isn't in our village.

786
00:44:50,623 --> 00:44:52,623
It must be a cell that only exists
in Soon-rok's village.

787
00:44:52,706 --> 00:44:54,372
He says he'll protect her.

788
00:44:54,456 --> 00:44:55,664
What does he plan to do?

789
00:45:07,331 --> 00:45:08,331
It's good, right?

790
00:45:11,164 --> 00:45:12,164
It's delicious.

791
00:45:15,247 --> 00:45:16,664
You have to eat the tteokbokki first.

792
00:45:16,748 --> 00:45:19,080
Then their Einspänner completes it.

793
00:45:19,539 --> 00:45:21,498
I discovered this place last year

794
00:45:21,581 --> 00:45:23,581
and it wasn't famous back then.

795
00:45:23,664 --> 00:45:25,664
But just six months later

796
00:45:25,748 --> 00:45:27,623
it got super famous.

797
00:45:32,914 --> 00:45:33,914
What's this?

798
00:45:34,247 --> 00:45:35,247
Your birthday present.

799
00:45:37,122 --> 00:45:38,830
You already gave me a birthday present.

800
00:45:39,498 --> 00:45:41,164
You paid for the whole trip.

801
00:45:41,247 --> 00:45:43,414
That was for my solo trip,
so it doesn't count as a gift.

802
00:45:45,372 --> 00:45:46,914
Oh, I'm fine, Soon-rok.

803
00:45:46,997 --> 00:45:47,997
Open it.

804
00:45:49,456 --> 00:45:50,456
You surprised me.

805
00:45:50,539 --> 00:45:51,997
I really wasn't expecting this.

806
00:45:53,456 --> 00:45:54,456
But what is it?

807
00:45:55,706 --> 00:45:57,122
This is an expensive brand.

808
00:45:58,664 --> 00:45:59,664
Is it earrings?

809
00:46:12,539 --> 00:46:13,539
It's a ring.

810
00:46:13,914 --> 00:46:14,914
Yes.

811
00:46:14,997 --> 00:46:15,997
A ring?

812
00:46:16,206 --> 00:46:18,080
A ring for a birthday present?

813
00:46:18,664 --> 00:46:19,830
A ring?

814
00:46:24,247 --> 00:46:25,664
Gosh, it's beautiful.

815
00:46:26,872 --> 00:46:27,872
But this is only

816
00:46:28,289 --> 00:46:30,080
- crystal, right?
-It's real.

817
00:46:31,997 --> 00:46:34,289
- It's real?
- Of course, it's real.

818
00:46:37,331 --> 00:46:39,164
This is a real diamond ring?

819
00:46:40,581 --> 00:46:42,830
You're giving me a diamond ring
for my birthday?

820
00:46:43,414 --> 00:46:46,331
- Try it on to check the size.
- Hold on.

821
00:46:47,747 --> 00:46:48,955
How much is this?

822
00:46:49,039 --> 00:46:50,289
I can tell just by looking at it.

823
00:46:52,456 --> 00:46:55,039
Who gives this as a birthday gift?

824
00:46:55,122 --> 00:46:56,122
It's too much.

825
00:46:56,414 --> 00:46:58,331
Why not? It's possible.

826
00:46:59,164 --> 00:47:00,289
It's pretty.

827
00:47:00,830 --> 00:47:01,955
What, you buy everything that's pretty?

828
00:47:02,372 --> 00:47:04,247
Is your family rich or something?

829
00:47:04,331 --> 00:47:05,498
You're not.

830
00:47:06,122 --> 00:47:08,039
I'm so flustered right now.

831
00:47:09,080 --> 00:47:10,914
Does buying something like this
mean nothing to you?

832
00:47:11,122 --> 00:47:12,664
I thought it would look good on you.

833
00:47:13,039 --> 00:47:15,164
So you'd just buy anything
if they look good on me?

834
00:47:15,247 --> 00:47:16,539
It's not that I just bought it.

835
00:47:17,039 --> 00:47:18,456
It's a birthday gift and...

836
00:47:19,705 --> 00:47:21,872
I was thinking of it
as an engagement ring.

837
00:47:22,663 --> 00:47:23,788
A proposal?

838
00:47:23,872 --> 00:47:25,122
A proposal?

839
00:47:27,705 --> 00:47:30,331
I'm so shocked I lost my appetite again.

840
00:47:30,414 --> 00:47:32,955
- Did I mishear?
- Hurry!

841
00:47:34,747 --> 00:47:36,414
Open the castle gates

842
00:47:36,872 --> 00:47:39,122
and welcome me!

843
00:47:41,872 --> 00:47:43,498
I will walk this one-way path for you

844
00:47:43,955 --> 00:47:45,872
for the rest of my life.

845
00:47:53,331 --> 00:47:54,331
Yu-mi?

846
00:47:56,456 --> 00:47:57,498
What if...

847
00:47:59,663 --> 00:48:01,080
we got married?

848
00:48:03,955 --> 00:48:05,663
I think it would be great.

849
00:48:07,997 --> 00:48:09,080
What do you think about it?

850
00:48:35,705 --> 00:48:40,372
EPISODE 24
THE THIRD PROPOSAL

851
00:48:44,788 --> 00:48:45,788
What do you...

852
00:48:46,539 --> 00:48:47,663
think about it?

853
00:49:04,414 --> 00:49:06,414
Soon-rok proposed.

854
00:49:06,498 --> 00:49:07,498
A proposal?

855
00:49:07,580 --> 00:49:09,164
While drinking an Einspänner.

856
00:49:09,247 --> 00:49:10,914
Hey, let's go, let's go!

857
00:49:12,622 --> 00:49:13,997
Let's hurry.

858
00:49:14,331 --> 00:49:15,788
Rational, where are you going?

859
00:49:16,164 --> 00:49:17,872
I heard Yu-mi got a proposal.

860
00:49:18,206 --> 00:49:20,080
There's something I need to check.
Follow me!

861
00:49:26,498 --> 00:49:27,872
The sudden proposal

862
00:49:27,955 --> 00:49:30,331
made her reflect
for the first time in a while.

863
00:49:31,914 --> 00:49:34,414
- A proposal... A proposal...
- Here it is.

864
00:49:36,997 --> 00:49:38,206
THE DAY YU-MI PROPOSED TO GU UNG

865
00:49:40,538 --> 00:49:43,289
There have been two proposals
in Yu-mi's life.

866
00:49:44,456 --> 00:49:45,830
The first proposal...

867
00:49:46,080 --> 00:49:47,080
Ung.

868
00:49:48,622 --> 00:49:49,622
Should we...

869
00:49:50,456 --> 00:49:51,498
get married?

870
00:49:54,247 --> 00:49:55,747
Yu-mi proposed first...

871
00:49:58,414 --> 00:50:00,122
but she never got an answer.

872
00:50:01,206 --> 00:50:02,497
I get it.

873
00:50:02,580 --> 00:50:03,830
I haven't said anything yet.

874
00:50:03,914 --> 00:50:06,039
I was just curious

875
00:50:06,122 --> 00:50:07,622
what you thought.

876
00:50:08,414 --> 00:50:10,622
You don't have to think about it so hard.

877
00:50:10,705 --> 00:50:12,663
The second proposal...

878
00:50:13,414 --> 00:50:14,414
Yu-mi...

879
00:50:16,497 --> 00:50:17,580
let's get...

880
00:50:18,372 --> 00:50:19,372
married.

881
00:50:22,039 --> 00:50:23,080
I'm sorry.

882
00:50:24,538 --> 00:50:25,663
I think I know what you mean.

883
00:50:30,039 --> 00:50:32,538
It ended with Yu-mi returning the ring.

884
00:50:32,997 --> 00:50:34,289
When was that?

885
00:50:34,580 --> 00:50:37,414
She proposed to Ung
after nine months of dating.

886
00:50:37,872 --> 00:50:40,247
She got a proposal from Ba-bi
after one year and four months.

887
00:50:40,747 --> 00:50:41,872
But what about Soon-rok now?

888
00:50:42,080 --> 00:50:43,122
After one month.

889
00:50:46,164 --> 00:50:47,497
It's way too rushed.

890
00:50:47,580 --> 00:50:48,914
This isn't right.

891
00:50:52,622 --> 00:50:54,788
Hunger. Give me a boost.

892
00:50:55,164 --> 00:50:56,164
Okay.

893
00:50:57,663 --> 00:50:59,830
What took you so long? I was waiting.

894
00:51:00,080 --> 00:51:01,997
Let's just say yes already.

895
00:51:02,580 --> 00:51:03,580
No.

896
00:51:04,039 --> 00:51:05,039
Huh? Why?

897
00:51:05,122 --> 00:51:08,206
Even when she thought she knew them

898
00:51:08,497 --> 00:51:10,331
it ended badly.

899
00:51:10,414 --> 00:51:12,247
But after only one month?

900
00:51:12,331 --> 00:51:13,705
It's too reckless.

901
00:51:13,788 --> 00:51:14,830
We have to turn him down.

902
00:51:15,080 --> 00:51:17,872
Hey, what if we miss our chance?

903
00:51:18,122 --> 00:51:19,372
What if he walks away?

904
00:51:20,914 --> 00:51:22,497
What if Soon-rok can't work up

905
00:51:22,580 --> 00:51:24,414
the courage to propose again?

906
00:51:24,580 --> 00:51:27,413
But we can't give him
an answer this hastily.

907
00:51:27,830 --> 00:51:29,372
Yu-mi isn't young anymore.

908
00:51:29,455 --> 00:51:31,122
Hey, that's enough!

909
00:51:32,039 --> 00:51:33,455
I'm stronger than you now!

910
00:51:34,872 --> 00:51:36,497
Let's answer quickly.

911
00:51:36,580 --> 00:51:39,622
The Einspänner is getting watery.

912
00:51:44,747 --> 00:51:45,872
What do you...

913
00:51:46,164 --> 00:51:47,413
think about it?

914
00:51:51,788 --> 00:51:52,955
Guys, stop!

915
00:51:53,247 --> 00:51:54,580
Emotional Cell is right.

916
00:51:54,663 --> 00:51:56,039
Love is all about timing.

917
00:51:56,372 --> 00:51:57,830
If Yu-mi loves Soon-rok

918
00:51:57,914 --> 00:51:59,914
there's no reason to hesitate.

919
00:52:00,663 --> 00:52:01,663
But...

920
00:52:01,747 --> 00:52:02,747
I'll decide.

921
00:52:04,372 --> 00:52:05,663
I, Love Cell!

922
00:52:06,039 --> 00:52:08,538
In the name of the Prime Cell,
I accept the proposal...

923
00:52:10,289 --> 00:52:11,289
Love!

924
00:52:11,497 --> 00:52:12,497
Love.

925
00:52:14,080 --> 00:52:16,080
Hey! Who said you could?

926
00:52:19,914 --> 00:52:21,371
I'm the Prime Cell!

927
00:52:21,955 --> 00:52:23,371
I'm the Prime Cell too.

928
00:52:23,455 --> 00:52:24,872
I'm the Prime Cell!

929
00:52:25,206 --> 00:52:26,622
I, Writer Cell,

930
00:52:27,206 --> 00:52:28,705
in the name of the Prime Cell

931
00:52:28,788 --> 00:52:30,122
object to this!

932
00:52:35,247 --> 00:52:36,705
Are you crazy?

933
00:52:36,997 --> 00:52:38,538
Do you know how far behind

934
00:52:38,622 --> 00:52:40,705
the manuscript is due to her dating?

935
00:52:40,997 --> 00:52:42,997
Why is she thinking about marriage
during serialization!

936
00:52:43,080 --> 00:52:45,872
Tell him to come back after it's all over.

937
00:52:46,413 --> 00:52:47,747
If Soon-rok gets his feelings hurt

938
00:52:47,830 --> 00:52:49,330
will you take responsibility?

939
00:52:49,997 --> 00:52:51,455
If he gets upset over a manuscript

940
00:52:51,538 --> 00:52:53,330
Soon-rok isn't fit to be an producer.

941
00:52:54,122 --> 00:52:55,497
Everyone.

942
00:52:55,788 --> 00:52:58,747
But I think we need to answer quickly.

943
00:52:58,872 --> 00:53:00,914
Too much time is passing.

944
00:53:11,289 --> 00:53:12,289
Yu-mi?

945
00:53:14,164 --> 00:53:15,371
Don't you want to

946
00:53:15,455 --> 00:53:17,080
marry me?

947
00:53:28,330 --> 00:53:29,413
You're getting a call.

948
00:53:29,497 --> 00:53:31,080
Is it from work? You should get it.

949
00:53:37,914 --> 00:53:39,164
Yes, hello?

950
00:53:39,247 --> 00:53:40,330
Have you left?

951
00:53:41,455 --> 00:53:43,914
Yes, I'm about to leave now too.

952
00:53:44,914 --> 00:53:46,039
I'm taking the airport bus.

953
00:53:47,580 --> 00:53:48,622
Let's meet at the counter.

954
00:53:49,538 --> 00:53:50,538
Okay.

955
00:53:53,330 --> 00:53:54,413
They all left?

956
00:53:54,497 --> 00:53:56,164
We have to get up.

957
00:53:56,247 --> 00:53:57,663
No, I'm not late.

958
00:53:57,747 --> 00:53:59,247
What if you miss the bus?

959
00:53:59,872 --> 00:54:01,413
- Let's hurry.
- Wait...

960
00:54:12,246 --> 00:54:13,413
Isn't that it?

961
00:54:15,080 --> 00:54:17,246
You can't get on if it's full.
Let's hurry.

962
00:54:18,039 --> 00:54:19,039
Soon-rok, hurry up.

963
00:54:24,788 --> 00:54:25,830
You won't be late, right?

964
00:54:26,164 --> 00:54:27,206
Call me when you get there.

965
00:54:28,955 --> 00:54:30,039
Oh, okay.

966
00:54:30,997 --> 00:54:32,663
- But...
- Safe trip.

967
00:54:32,830 --> 00:54:33,830
Go on.

968
00:54:53,288 --> 00:54:55,580
Let's talk later.

969
00:55:40,622 --> 00:55:42,080
Let go.

970
00:55:59,580 --> 00:56:00,580
But...

971
00:56:00,663 --> 00:56:03,246
we didn't get Yu-mi's answer.

972
00:56:27,997 --> 00:56:30,914
I think Soon-rok is upset right now.

973
00:56:44,371 --> 00:56:46,497
Do you think Soon-rok's feelings are hurt?

974
00:56:46,955 --> 00:56:48,080
I think so.

975
00:56:49,205 --> 00:56:51,080
Yu-mi's feelings were hurt too.

976
00:56:51,580 --> 00:56:52,580
When?

977
00:56:53,288 --> 00:56:55,538
When Ung didn't give an answer...

978
00:56:56,705 --> 00:57:00,538
I think I know now
why Ung couldn't answer.

979
00:57:01,497 --> 00:57:03,497
It wasn't that he didn't love Yu-mi

980
00:57:03,830 --> 00:57:05,914
but he had too much to think about.

981
00:57:08,205 --> 00:57:09,997
I was so upset back then

982
00:57:11,205 --> 00:57:13,079
but now I understand.

983
00:57:14,455 --> 00:57:15,622
But he lost Yu-mi

984
00:57:15,705 --> 00:57:18,830
because he thought too much.

985
00:57:19,079 --> 00:57:20,079
There's such a thing

986
00:57:20,163 --> 00:57:21,455
as timing in love.

987
00:57:21,955 --> 00:57:23,788
If you miss it, it's hard to get back.

988
00:57:25,246 --> 00:57:26,288
That's true too.

989
00:57:37,955 --> 00:57:38,955
But...

990
00:57:39,038 --> 00:57:40,663
if you rashly put it on
and you change your mind...

991
00:57:42,872 --> 00:57:44,455
Putting it on and giving it back

992
00:57:44,538 --> 00:57:46,663
would really hurt the other person.

993
00:57:47,663 --> 00:57:50,413
That's worse than
never putting it on at all.

994
00:57:50,955 --> 00:57:52,288
Are you going to inflict that pain again?

995
00:58:03,622 --> 00:58:05,246
Then what should we do?

996
00:58:05,538 --> 00:58:06,622
The more Soon-rok is like this

997
00:58:06,705 --> 00:58:08,121
the more careful we need to be.

998
00:58:08,788 --> 00:58:10,079
Yu-mi is the older one.

999
00:58:13,914 --> 00:58:16,330
Let's not make the same mistake again.

1000
00:58:16,663 --> 00:58:18,121
This is the third proposal.

1001
00:58:35,413 --> 00:58:36,455
It's raining.

1002
00:58:57,413 --> 00:58:59,079
SHIN SOON-ROK PD

1003
00:59:07,038 --> 00:59:08,288
Hey, Soon-rok.

1004
00:59:08,622 --> 00:59:09,622
Yu-mi.

1005
00:59:09,914 --> 00:59:11,996
Did you get there okay?
Are you on the plane?

1006
00:59:12,497 --> 00:59:13,538
No.

1007
00:59:13,788 --> 00:59:14,788
Then?

1008
00:59:14,872 --> 00:59:15,872
I'm...

1009
00:59:15,954 --> 00:59:17,246
outside your place right now.

1010
00:59:23,371 --> 00:59:24,413
My flight

1011
00:59:24,954 --> 00:59:26,580
was canceled due to an engine malfunction.

1012
00:59:26,872 --> 00:59:29,038
My new flight is tomorrow, so I came back.

1013
00:59:29,580 --> 00:59:31,205
How could something like that happen?

1014
00:59:31,455 --> 00:59:32,455
Yu-mi.

1015
00:59:32,538 --> 00:59:34,121
Can I stop by for a bit?

1016
00:59:34,246 --> 00:59:35,788
Yes, come on in.

1017
00:59:36,205 --> 00:59:37,205
Okay, I'm coming up.

1018
00:59:43,246 --> 00:59:44,288
Thank you.

1019
00:59:48,038 --> 00:59:50,371
He's throwing all the proposals
in at once!

1020
00:59:50,663 --> 00:59:53,830
What do I do?
I was just glad I had time to think.

1021
00:59:53,913 --> 00:59:55,205
What should we say?

1022
00:59:55,622 --> 00:59:57,455
Yu-mi hasn't decided on an answer yet.

1023
01:00:02,538 --> 01:00:03,705
Yu-mi.

1024
01:00:03,788 --> 01:00:05,163
Did you get caught in the rain?

1025
01:00:05,580 --> 01:00:07,622
I should've come out with an umbrella.

1026
01:00:07,872 --> 01:00:09,663
- Hang on. I'll get you a towel.
- Okay.

1027
01:00:30,038 --> 01:00:32,413
- Thank you.
- All that traveling must be tiring.

1028
01:00:34,079 --> 01:00:35,205
I am tired.

1029
01:00:35,705 --> 01:00:36,830
Aren't you hungry?

1030
01:00:37,246 --> 01:00:39,580
Do you have anything cold to drink?

1031
01:00:41,580 --> 01:00:43,288
- Should I make you an ade?
- That sounds good.

1032
01:00:46,871 --> 01:00:48,455
What time are you leaving tomorrow?

1033
01:00:48,871 --> 01:00:50,121
It's a morning flight.

1034
01:00:50,205 --> 01:00:51,205
I have to leave at six.

1035
01:00:52,121 --> 01:00:53,288
You're leaving at dawn.

1036
01:00:55,371 --> 01:00:56,580
I'll give you a ride tomorrow.

1037
01:01:05,205 --> 01:01:06,205
Yu-mi.

1038
01:01:06,580 --> 01:01:07,580
Yes?

1039
01:01:07,663 --> 01:01:08,663
Should I...

1040
01:01:09,121 --> 01:01:10,121
return this?

1041
01:01:13,371 --> 01:01:15,205
- What?
- If you feel burdened by it

1042
01:01:16,246 --> 01:01:17,246
I can...

1043
01:01:17,580 --> 01:01:18,622
return it.

1044
01:01:25,747 --> 01:01:26,747
Why...

1045
01:01:26,829 --> 01:01:28,455
I got carried away and bought it

1046
01:01:29,205 --> 01:01:31,163
but you seem to feel burdened by it.

1047
01:01:35,747 --> 01:01:37,038
If you say you're not ready...

1048
01:01:37,330 --> 01:01:38,330
I...

1049
01:01:38,497 --> 01:01:39,497
can wait.

1050
01:01:41,788 --> 01:01:42,871
I just...

1051
01:01:44,038 --> 01:01:46,788
I was so sure
that we would end up getting married

1052
01:01:47,829 --> 01:01:49,622
that I bought it
without thinking too much.

1053
01:01:50,871 --> 01:01:51,871
That...

1054
01:01:54,330 --> 01:01:56,079
How can you be so sure?

1055
01:01:57,622 --> 01:02:00,787
We've only known
each other a month, Soon-rok.

1056
01:02:02,871 --> 01:02:05,413
We don't even know each other that well.

1057
01:02:07,163 --> 01:02:09,121
How can you be so sure about that?

1058
01:02:12,246 --> 01:02:13,497
If I wasn't sure...

1059
01:02:14,622 --> 01:02:16,163
I wouldn't have run to you
in the first place.

1060
01:02:21,288 --> 01:02:22,829
If I wasn't sure back then...

1061
01:02:28,330 --> 01:02:29,371
Shin PD?

1062
01:02:30,413 --> 01:02:32,205
I wouldn't have gone to see you again.

1063
01:02:34,246 --> 01:02:35,288
Since then

1064
01:02:36,413 --> 01:02:37,580
you've been sure?

1065
01:02:38,954 --> 01:02:40,787
- Yes.
- That certainty...

1066
01:02:41,246 --> 01:02:42,497
where does it come from?

1067
01:02:43,538 --> 01:02:44,663
Because I can just tell.

1068
01:02:45,663 --> 01:02:46,746
How do you know?

1069
01:02:47,330 --> 01:02:48,455
How do I know?

1070
01:02:49,455 --> 01:02:50,455
Yes.

1071
01:02:51,705 --> 01:02:52,746
In my entire life...

1072
01:02:54,787 --> 01:02:55,871
it's the first time

1073
01:02:56,246 --> 01:02:57,705
I've ever felt this way.

1074
01:03:01,705 --> 01:03:02,871
That's how I know.

1075
01:03:54,787 --> 01:03:57,622
The reason love is always surprising

1076
01:03:59,455 --> 01:04:03,079
is because no two loves are ever the same.

1077
01:04:05,704 --> 01:04:07,038
So...

1078
01:04:07,746 --> 01:04:10,330
Soon-rok is a different person.

1079
01:04:12,246 --> 01:04:14,580
For a man whose values on love
are completely different

1080
01:04:15,996 --> 01:04:19,121
what's the point of applying
my own past experiences?

1081
01:04:20,455 --> 01:04:22,580
That was the thought that crossed my mind.

1082
01:04:39,538 --> 01:04:40,580
Then, Soon-rok.

1083
01:04:43,371 --> 01:04:44,455
Let's do as you say.

1084
01:04:46,538 --> 01:04:47,538
What?

1085
01:04:49,829 --> 01:04:50,871
Let's return...

1086
01:04:51,871 --> 01:04:52,913
the ring.

1087
01:04:55,038 --> 01:04:56,038
I...

1088
01:04:57,413 --> 01:04:59,580
like you so much right now.

1089
01:05:01,371 --> 01:05:03,246
But I think I still need some time.

1090
01:05:05,704 --> 01:05:08,746
I feel like I need to.

1091
01:05:10,662 --> 01:05:13,079
-Yu-mi, you don't have to feel...
-So...

1092
01:05:13,996 --> 01:05:15,330
when that time comes...

1093
01:05:17,246 --> 01:05:18,371
I'll tell you too.

1094
01:05:21,538 --> 01:05:22,538
Okay.

1095
01:05:22,954 --> 01:05:25,246
But the ring...

